      "question": "Find the area of a sector of a circle with radius $6$ $cm$ if the angle of the sector is $60^\\circ$.",
      "answer": "$\\frac{132}{7}$ $cm^2$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the formula for the area of a sector $A = \\frac{\\theta}{360^\\circ} \\times \\pi r^2$.",
          "Substitute $\\theta = 60^\\circ$, $r = 6$ $cm$, and $\\pi = \\frac{22}{7}$ to calculate the area."
        ],
        "derivation": "A = \\frac{60^\\circ}{360^\\circ} \\times \\frac{22}{7} \\times 6^2 \\Rightarrow A = \\frac{1}{6} \\times \\frac{22}{7} \\times 36 \\Rightarrow A = 6 \\times \\frac{22}{7} = \\frac{132}{7} \\text{ cm}^2"
      },
