      "question": "Find the area of a quadrant of a circle whose circumference is $44$ $cm$.",
      "answer": "$38.5$ $cm^2$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the circumference $2\\pi r = 44$ to find the radius $r$.",
          "Calculate the area of the quadrant using $\\frac{1}{4} \\pi r^2$."
        ],
        "derivation": "2 \\times \\frac{22}{7} \\times r = 44 \\Rightarrow r = 7 \\text{ cm} \\Rightarrow \\text{Area} = \\frac{1}{4} \\times \\frac{22}{7} \\times 7^2 \\Rightarrow \\text{Area} = \\frac{1}{4} \\times 22 \\times 7 = \\frac{154}{4} = 38.5 \\text{ cm}^2"
      },
